\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 8. What is your approach to representing calving? What calving law or calving rate is used? Do you use any subgrid-scale schemes? How are the parameters of the calving law calibrated? \
\
Ice front position is prescribed via a level-set spclevelset time series built\
from the ISMIP7 annual ice-shelf-collapse mask\
(fracture/ice_shelf_collapse_mask_<model>_<scenario>_ismip7_8km.nc; source:\
Greene et al., AntarcticaObsISMIP7-v1.2 for the historical period).\
The mask is made cumulative so that once a shelf collapses it remains\
constrained for the rest of the simulation.  No dynamic calving law is used;\
the calving rate is set to zero and front migration is entirely controlled by\
the prescribed levelset.
\f1\fs24 \
\
